# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok as the clinton administration 's freshest face , budget director frank raines , prefers <unk> .
# ::alignments
(p / prefer-01
      :ARG0 (p2 / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Frank"
                  :op2 "Raines")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG2 (d / director
                        :topic (b / budget)))
            :ARG0-of (h2 / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (g / government-organization
                        :ARG0-of (a / administrate-01)
                        :mod (p3 / person
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Clinton")))))
      :ARG1 (p4 / person
            :name (n3 / name
                  :op1 "Izzat"))
      :ARG1-of (r / resemble-01
            :ARG2 (f / face
                  :ARG1-of (h3 / have-degree-91
                        :ARG2 (f2 / fresh-04
                              :ARG1 f)
                        :ARG3 (m / most)))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok all ## crew members on board a chinese cargo ship sinking off the danish coast have been rescued after the vessel collided with another freighter , danish maritime rescuers said saturday .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (r / rescue-01
                  :ARG1 (s2 / sea
                        :mod (c / country
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "Denmark")))))
      :ARG1 (r2 / rescue-01
            :ARG1 (p2 / person
                  :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG1 (c2 / crew)
                        :ARG2 (m / member))
                  :mod (a / all)
                  :location (b / board-01
                        :ARG1 (s3 / ship
                              :mod (c3 / cargo)
                              :mod (c4 / country
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "China"))
                              :ARG1-of (s4 / sink-01
                                    :location (o / off
                                          :op1 (c5 / coast
                                                :part-of c))))))
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (s5 / saturday))
            :time (a2 / after
                  :op1 (c6 / collide-01
                        :ARG0 s3
                        :ARG1 (f / freighter
                              :mod (a3 / another))))))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok father 's day rolls around june ## , a little more than a week from now .
# ::alignments
(r / roll-01
      :ARG1 (d / day
            :poss (p / person
                  :ARG0-of (h / have-rel-role-91
                        :ARG2 (f / father))))
      :direction (a / around)
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :month 5)
      :time (a2 / after
            :op1 (n / now)
            :quant (m / more-than
                  :op1 (t / temporal-quantity
                        :quant 1
                        :unit (w / week))
                  :degree (l / little))))

# ::id 3 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok more than half of us companies do not allow employees to visit social networks such as facebook , myspace or twitter while at work , according to a new survey .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (s2 / survey-01
            :ARG1-of (n / new-01))
      :ARG1 (a / allow-01
            :polarity -
            :ARG0 (c / company
                  :ARG1-of (ii / include-91
                        :ARG2 (c2 / company
                              :domain (w / we))
                        :ARG3 (m / more-than
                              :op1 "1/2")))
            :ARG1 (v / visit-01
                  :ARG0 (p / person
                        :ARG1-of (e / employ-01))
                  :ARG1 (n2 / network
                        :mod (s3 / social)
                        :example (o / or
                              :op1 (p2 / publication
                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "Facebook"))
                              :op2 (p3 / publication
                                    :name (n4 / name
                                          :op1 "Myspace"))
                              :op3 (p4 / publication
                                    :name (n5 / name
                                          :op1 "Twitter"))))
                  :time (w2 / work-01
                        :ARG0 p))))

# ::id 4 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok when two friends met for cocktails on wednesday night at the safari club , a popular saloon in this town southeast of portland , sparks began to fly when the topic turned to the senate ethics committee 's accusations of sexual misconduct against sen. bob packwood .
# ::alignments
(b / begin-01
      :ARG1 (f / fly-01
            :ARG1 (s / spark-01))
      :time (m / meet-03
            :ARG0 (p / person
                  :quant 2
                  :ARG0-of (h / have-rel-role-91
                        :ARG2 (f2 / friend))
                  :ARG1-of h)
            :purpose (c / cocktail)
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (w / wednesday)
                  :dayperiod (n / night))
            :location (c2 / club
                  :mod (s2 / safari)
                  :location (s3 / saloon
                        :ARG1-of (p2 / popular-02)
                        :location (t / town
                              :mod (t2 / this)
                              :location (r / relative-position
                                    :op1 (p3 / portland)
                                    :direction (s4 / southeast))))))
      :time (t3 / turn-02
            :ARG1 (t4 / topic)
            :ARG2 (a / accuse-01
                  :ARG0 (c3 / committee
                        :topic (e / ethics)
                        :part-of (g / government-organization
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Senate")))
                  :ARG1 (p4 / person
                        :name (n3 / name
                              :op1 "Bob"
                              :op2 "Packwood")
                        :ARG0-of (h2 / have-org-role-91
                              :ARG2 (s5 / senator)))
                  :ARG2 (m2 / misconduct-01
                        :ARG0 p4
                        :ARG1 (s6 / sex-01
                              :ARG0 p4)))))

# ::id 5 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok kurt vonnegut , the satirical novelist who captured the absurdity of war and questioned the advances of science in darkly humorous works such as `` slaughterhouse-five '' and `` cat 's cradle , '' died wednesday .
# ::alignments
(d / die-01
      :ARG1 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Kurt"
                  :op2 "vonnegut")
            :ARG0-of (w / write-01
                  :manner (s / satire))
            :ARG0-of (c / capture-01
                  :ARG1 (a / absurd
                        :domain (w2 / war-01)))
            :ARG0-of (q / question-03
                  :ARG1 (a2 / advance-01
                        :ARG1 (s2 / science))
                  :medium (w3 / work-01
                        :example (a3 / and
                              :op1 (s3 / slaughterhouse-five)
                              :op2 (c2 / cradle
                                    :poss (c3 / cat)))
                        :ARG0-of (h / humor-01
                              :manner (d2 / darkly)))))
      :time (w4 / wednesday))

                  :ARG1 (c / country
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Honduras"))
                  :ARG2 (m / minister
                        :topic (d / defend-01))))
      :ARG1 (d2 / destroy-01
            :ARG0 (f / fire)
            :ARG1 (f2 / forest
                  :quant (a / at-least
                        :op1 (a2 / area-quantity
                              :quant 1000000
                              :unit (h2 / hectare))))
            :time (s2 / since
                  :op1 (b / begin-01
                        :ARG1 (y / year
                              :mod (t / this)))))
      :time (d3 / date-entity
            :weekday (t2 / tuesday)))

                  :mod (t / team
                        :name (n3 / name
                              :op1 "Atlanta")))
            :ARG1-of (c / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (h / hit-01
                        :ARG0 p
                        :ARG1 (p2 / person
                              :name (n4 / name
                                    :op1 "Paul"
                                    :op2 "Ranger")
                              :ARG0-of (h2 / have-org-role-91
                                    :ARG1 (t2 / team
                                          :name (n5 / name
                                                :op1 "Tampa"
                                                :op2 "Bay"))
                                    :ARG2 (d / defenseman)))
                        :mod (v / vicious))))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (f / friday)))
